AGI - A woman who brought a corpse to a wheelchair in a bank in Rio de Janeiro> to try to withdraw a loan on behalf of the deceased is &nbsp;> is formally accused of vilipendium of corpse and attempted theft with fraud > . Erika de Souza Vieira Nunes, whose unusual attempt of fraud recorded in video by an employee of the bank>&nbsp; became viral on social networks, was arrested in scourgency and formally accused of the two counts, declared the Civil Police of the Brazilian city. The events took place on Tuesday afternoon in a banking agency in Bangù, a populous neighborhood in the western part of Rio de Janeiro, where the accused, 42 years old, arrived bringing with him the body of a 68-year-old man, identified as Paulo Roberto Braga, on a wheelchair.
&nbsp;
Vieira Nunes, who had to keep the head of the corpse standing all the time to avoid collapse, tried to complete the practices for a loan of 17,000 reais (about $3,333) that the man had virtually demanded and to withdraw the money.&nbsp; Although the woman claims to be the nephew and the man's caregiver and that these were alive when he arrived at the bank, the experts claimed to be the man's nephew and the man' The employees of the bank were alarmed for what they considered the serious state of health of the applicant the loan and called the emergency services, which confirmed the death.
&nbsp;
< blockquote
| En un hecho insólito en Bangu, Río de Janeiro, Érika de Souza Vieira Nunes fue descubierta intent retirar un préstamo bankingus using el cadáver de su tío, Paulo Roberto Braga, de 68 años.<a href="https://t.co/IyGeG0Ax5X"
