AGI - It will be the crisis in the Middle East the main topic on the agenda of the G7 Foreign Minister who begins today in Capri and ends Friday. The ministry falls at a time of particular tension, after the attack on the Saturday of Iran in Israel, in fear of an Israeli reaction, the drama of the war in Gaza and the hostages in the hands of Hamas, and the dossier 'Red Sea' that hinders the world traffics. The Italian government has long reiterated its appeals to de-escalation and moderation, an appeal to both sides. Today the vice-premier, Antonio Tajani, who met yesterday in Rome the ambassadors of the Arab League and the Organization for Islamic Cooperation, has assured that the Italian G7 intends, indeed "it has the task of working for peace". "The government is committed to an all-round effort to achieve this," he said, optimistic: "We are sure that the Capri meeting will make an important contribution." He will discuss this at closed doors with the US Secretary of State, Antony Blinken; and the Head of Foreign Affairs of Germany, Annalena Baerbock; of Canada, Me'lanie Joly; that of Quai d'Orsay, Caterina Colonna; of Japan, Yoshifumi Tsuge, and of the United Kingdom, David Cameron. The government's stated goal is to strengthen the role of the G7 as a place for dialogue of liberal democracies and the composition of the crises that never as now upset the world.
&nbsp;
In this regard, for the crisis in the Middle East, in addition to addressing the issue of the humanitarian crisis in Gaza and that of the hostages, the attempt will be to relaunch a political process for the solution 'two peoples two states'. Tajani, who in the late afternoon will welcome the delegations, today should also have a 'face-to-face' with the head of American diplomacy, Antony Blinken. The meeting will also be an opportunity to discuss the response to Russian aggression to Ukraine: Tajani invited his Ukrainian colleague, Dmytro Kuleba, and NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg to Capri. The support of Ukraine is not discussed, even in this case we will try to define a path that, in addition to giving full political, financial and military support in Kiev, can lead to "a just and lasting peace". The main focus of the session will be the strengthening of the G7 partnership with the Continent.
<div </div
The G7 ministers will also discuss the establishment of the Indo-Pacific region, the region which records the growing Chinese threat to Taiwan's independence, and which is, however, a priority for political balances and world trade; and major global issues such as infrastructure connectivity, cybersecurity, Artificial Intelligence and the fight against disinformation. Blinken anticipated that, in addition to the themes mentioned above, he has particular interest in stabilisation in Haiti and to deepen "mes of mutual interest" as the fight against climate change. The real works will begin tomorrow morning, at the Grand Hotel Quisisana, in the centre of Capri, a stone's throw from the 'piazzetta', the lounge of the island, and will end on Friday with the final press conference of Tajani. For the occasion the island-joyello, icon of the Italian beauties, is armored.
